# AIPIFY LAYER OWNERSHIP RULE

Before implementing ANY new feature, Cursor MUST determine which architectural layer owns the feature.

No implementation may proceed until ownership has been explicitly identified.

See also [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) for repo path mapping (`/platform`, `/app`, `/api/install`).

## LAYER 1 — PLATFORM ADMIN

**Purpose:** Used exclusively by Aipify Group AS to operate the SaaS platform itself.

**Allowed responsibilities:**

- Customer management
- Subscription management
- Billing oversight
- Invoice management
- Installation management
- Install Engine orchestration
- Update scheduling and rollout
- Trust & Security governance
- Platform-wide metrics
- Global support monitoring
- Automation templates
- Intelligence review
- Learning approval workflows
- Action approvals
- Skill marketplace governance
- System health monitoring
- Global anonymised impact metrics
- License administration
- Audit logs

**Must NEVER contain:**

- Customer business workflows
- Customer support inboxes
- Customer sales dashboards
- Customer operational tasks
- Customer internal automations

**Route examples:** `/platform/*`, `/platform/customers`, `/platform/intelligence`, `/platform/installations`

**Code:** `app/platform/`, `components/platform/`, `lib/platform/`

## LAYER 2 — CUSTOMER APP

**Purpose:** The operational workspace purchased and used by the customer.

**Allowed responsibilities:**

- Executive dashboard
- Morning briefings
- Customer support management
- Customer automations
- Customer approvals
- Customer recommendations
- Customer reports
- Customer skills
- Customer communications
- Internal business workflows
- Tenant-specific analytics
- Customer health summaries

**Must NEVER contain:**

- Other customer data
- Platform-wide metrics
- Platform billing management
- Global intelligence governance

**Route examples:** `/app/*`, `/app/executive`, `/app/support`, `/app/automations`

**Code:** `app/app/`, `components/app/`, `lib/app/`

## LAYER 3 — INSTALL ENGINE

**Purpose:** The installation layer responsible for learning and connecting safely with customer environments.

**Allowed responsibilities:**

- Integration discovery
- API connection setup
- Environment scanning
- Permission validation
- Health monitoring
- Installation templates
- Rollout preparation
- Upgrade compatibility checks
- Feature activation
- Local metadata collection

**Must NEVER contain:**

- Customer business decision making
- Global customer administration
- Platform billing logic

**Route examples:** `/api/install/*`, `/api/embed/*`

**Code:** `app/api/install/`, `app/api/embed/`, `lib/install/`, `lib/embed/`, `components/embed/`

## IMPLEMENTATION REQUIREMENT

Before generating code, Cursor MUST declare:

- `Feature owner: PLATFORM ADMIN`
- `Feature owner: CUSTOMER APP`
- `Feature owner: INSTALL ENGINE`

## CROSS-LAYER RULES

- Features may communicate across layers ONLY through approved APIs.
- Layers must remain independently deployable.
- No direct database access across tenants.
- No shared business logic without documented ownership.

## DUPLICATION RULE

Features must never be duplicated across layers unless there is documented justification.

**Example:** Executive Dashboard may exist in:

- **PLATFORM ADMIN** → Platform KPIs
- **CUSTOMER APP** → Customer business KPIs

These are separate implementations.

## DATA OWNERSHIP RULE

Customer operational data belongs to the customer.

**Platform Admin may only access:**

- Subscription status
- Installation status
- Licensing status
- Aggregated anonymised metrics
- System health information

**Platform Admin must NEVER access:**

- Customer emails
- Customer chats
- Customer sales records
- Customer inventory details
- Customer financial transactions

…unless explicitly authorised by the customer through controlled support workflows.

## GOLDEN RULE

If Cursor cannot clearly determine ownership, **STOP IMPLEMENTATION** and request clarification before proceeding.

Architecture must always take priority over speed of delivery.
